               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; incipit of Texts I-III; directives to the ministers and their abbreviations; titles of books to be read; elements of the punctuation signs; halle luya “Hallelujah”, ʾǝsmä lä-ʿaläm “since for eternity”, sǝmʿanni “listen” in Text III (fols. 3ra-7ra); ʾǝgäle in Text III, ʾamen “Amen” and its abbreviation in Text III (fols. 94vb-104rb); elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
On the incipit page of Text III (fols. 36vb), two lines are rubricated (alternating with a black line).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
